        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 1:09PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 109 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Sayre, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Elk City...                       Sayre...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
